<h4>Sound Voltex</h4>
                    <br>
                    for the populare arcade rythm game sound voltex there are alot of different types of setups you can use. <br>
                    <br>
                    for starter, there are a couple different types of  controllers you can use. <br>
                    for example.
                    <br>
                    asc (arcade size controller) <br><br>

                    <a href="https://www.gamo2.com/en/index.php?dispatch=products.view&product_id=393" style="color: white;">faucetwo+ by gamo2</a> <br> <br>
                    <a href="https://yuancon.store/controller/controller" style="color: white;">sdvx 12 by yuancon</a> <br> <br>
                    <a  href="https://yuancon.store/controller/sdvxlite" style="color: white;">sdvx lite 3 by yuancon</a> <br>
                    
                    <br>

                    you also have pico controllers such as. <br><br>

                    <a href="https://www.gamo2.com/en/index.php?dispatch=products.view&product_id=396" style="color: white;">faucetwo portable edition by gamo2</a> <br>
                    <a href="https://www.speedylabs.us/product/pocket-sdvx-pico-assembled/" style="color: white;">pocket sdvx pico v5 by Speedlabs</a> <br>
                    <br>

                    you could also make your own controllers by using one of the provided resources there are on github. <br>
